text: Misapata (Quechua misa table, pata elevated place; above, at the top; edge, bank, shore,Yachakuqkunapa Simi Qullqa - Qusqu Qullaw. Qhichwa Simipi (monolingual Quechua and bilingual Quechua-Spanish dictionary) also spelled Mesapata) is a mountain in the Andes of Peru, about high. It is situated in the Ayacucho Region, Lucanas Province, on the border of the districts of Cabana and Lucanas. It lies southwest of Anqasi and Inka Wasi. == References == Category:Mountains of Peru Category:Mountains of Ayacucho Region
